<h2 id="tell-me-about-yourself" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#tell-me-about-yourself"><span>Tell Me About Yourself</span></a></h2>
<h3 id="alternatives" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#alternatives"><span>Alternatives</span></a></h3>
<ul>
<li>“Can you walk us through your resume?”</li>
<li>“Please describe yourself.”</li>
<li>“What do you consider to be your biggest professional achievement?”</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="why-they-ask" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#why-they-ask"><span>Why They Ask?</span></a></h3>
<p>They are not asking for your life story. They want to quickly understand:</p>
<ul>
<li>Who are you professionally? Are you a backend engineer, full-stack engineer, systems person, or generalist?</li>
<li>Can you communicate clearly? Candidates need to explain technical work simply and confidently.</li>
<li>What should they ask next? Your answer guides the interview.</li>
<li>Are you relevant to this role? They want to know whether your background matches the role.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="strategy" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#strategy"><span>Strategy</span></a></h3>
<ol>
<li>Give a snapshot of your work history. (Company name, role, years, responsibilities)</li>
<li>Make your mini-stories achievement-oriented.</li>
<li>Transition into what you know about the role and what you’re looking to do next .</li>
<li>Tell why you’re interested in this position and why you are the right fit for what they need.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="tips" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#tips"><span>Tips</span></a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Introduction是面试成败的关键，一定要 <strong>Tailor</strong> Your Answer to the Role and Company，Top sentence开头, 关键词提取，重要技能埋点，方便面试中间进一步讨论。</li>
<li>Professional NOT Personal.
<ul>
<li>Don’t tell your life story.</li>
<li>Focus on being brief in your answer of how you are professionally equipped.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Be BRIEF.
<ul>
<li>Don’t list your resume; covers important points without rambling.</li>
<li>Emphasize the most important experiences &amp; aspects of you that address TECHNICAL skills from the job description.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Flow like a story.</li>
</ul>
